Echography in the study of adenopathies of the upper abdomen. Four-hundred eighty-five patients underwent US examination 183 of them had gastric cancer, 239 colorectal cancer, 38 pancreatic cancer, 11 esophageal cancer, and 14 had gastric lymphoma. All patients underwent surgery. In 95 cases fine-needle biopsy under US guidance was performed. Lymphadenopathies were classified by the criteria proposed by Yoshinaka et al., type I: poorly-defined borders, diffuse internal echoes